### PHP if-else Statement

The `if-else` statement executes one block of code if a condition is true and another block if the condition is false.

### Syntax

```php
<?php
if (condition) {
    // code if condition is true
} else {
    // code if condition is false
}
?>
```

### Examples

```php
<?php
$num = 10;

if ($num > 0) {
    echo "$num is positive";
} elseif ($num < 0) {
    echo "$num is negative";
} else {
    echo "$num is zero";
}
?>
```

### Nested if

```php
<?php
$age = 20;
$hasID = true;

if ($age >= 18) {
    if ($hasID) {
        echo "Entry allowed";
    } else {
        echo "ID required";
    }
} else {
    echo "Too young";
}
?>
```

> **Key Point:** You can nest `if` statements inside other `if` statements, but consider using logical operators to avoid deep nesting.
